From: CharlieChen114514 <725610365@qq.com>
Date: Thu, 17 Jul 2026 03:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: dts: rockchip: rk3506: fix MDIO -EBUSY by dropping
 snps,dwmac-mdio compatible from mdio nodes

The stmmac platform driver already creates and registers an MDIO bus
internally in stmmac_mdio_register().  When the mdio child node carries
compatible = "snps,dwmac-mdio", the kernel's of_platform_populate()
also spawns a separate platform device for the node.  Both code paths
try to register a bus with the same ID and the second one fails:

  rk_gmac-dwmac ff4c8000.ethernet: error -EBUSY: Cannot register the MDIO bus
  rk_gmac-dwmac ff4c8000.ethernet: error -EBUSY: MDIO bus (id: 0) registration failed

Drop the explicit compatible so that stmmac uses the mdio child node
only as a container for PHY discovery (of_mdiobus_register) without
triggering a duplicate platform-device probe.

The #address-cells / #size-cells remain because they are still needed
for the PHY sub-nodes.

Signed-off-by: CharlieChen114514 <725610365@qq.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3506.dtsi | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3506.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3506.dtsi
@@ -314,7 +314,6 @@
 		status = "disabled";
 
 		mdio0: mdio {
-			compatible = "snps,dwmac-mdio";
 			#address-cells = <0x1>;
 			#size-cells = <0x0>;
 		};
@@ -368,7 +367,6 @@
 		status = "disabled";
 
 		mdio1: mdio {
-			compatible = "snps,dwmac-mdio";
 			#address-cells = <0x1>;
 			#size-cells = <0x0>;
 		};
